startDriverSocket() - Method in class org.jppf.process.ProcessLauncher
Start a server socket that will accept one connection at a time with the JPPF driver, so the server can shutdown properly, when this driver is killed, by a way other than the API (ie CTRL-C or killing the process through the OS shell).
The port the server socket listens to is dynamically attributed, which is obtained by using the constructor new ServerSocket(0).

The single connection at a time is obtained by doing the ServerSocket.accept() and the Socket.getInputStream().read() in the same thread.
